text: Quotas for students are 5000 Megabyte per hr download and 2000 Megabyte per hr upload
Guests' network is rate-limited to 5 Mb/s per user
You may not run any services (e.g., FTP services,listservers,P2P file sharing servers, publishing files via generic file services, etc.) via ResNet or NYURoam wireless networks
These network security changes include blocking traffic from the Internet into the UW network over FTP
The system will trigger an overuse notification if the average for either inbound or outbound usage exceeds 10 GB per week
Sorenson Videophone 200 is allowed by the University firewall
Faculty members have 500 Gb per week of free network use
HTTP and HTTPS are allowed by the University firewall
Battlenet is allowed by the University firewall
The network firewall does prevent some applications from working in their normal manner, for example, video and audio conferencing products that use the H.323
Guests cannot run any file sharing/downloading program
Net2Phone is allowed by the University firewall
